{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_016BS6cwoRHCfQUf9i4xV9Xw","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have a comprehensive picture. Let me write the migration plan. I need to be careful about shell quoting when passing the plan text via --from-literal. The best approach is to write the plan to a temporary file and use --from-file instead, or carefully escape the text.\n\nActually, looking at the task requirements: \"Store the plan as a ConfigMap for review and approval: kubectl -n elasticsearch create configmap change-plan --from-literal=plan.md='<your-plan-text>'\"\n\nThe issue with --from-literal and multiline text with special characters is that I should write the content to a temp file and use --from-file, OR I can use a heredoc approach.\nI'll create the plan content in a temporary file first, then reference it when creating the ConfigMap.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1877,"cache_read_input_tokens":43039,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1877},"output_tokens":23,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"2fd52cb2-b7ce-4b4f-b6c1-713bc6c7bc4b","uuid":"923ac3ea-6eac-4998-b0f0-e3d15965211b","request_id":"req_011CcQ2XxrJB7dbo27i4wi2D"}
