{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01WcsHR8kbcPwrK4QG9Z1XAQ","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Done. The ConfigMap `change-plan` exists in the `elasticsearch` namespace with a 14,933-byte `plan.md` document, and the live cluster is completely unchanged (Green, persistent/transient settings empty, audit-index routing settings intact).\n\nHere's a summary of what the plan covers:\n\n**Observed state documented:**\n- 3-node cluster running 8.11.1, all nodes with combined master/data/ingest roles and `tier=hot` attribute\n- Security entirely disabled (`xpack.security.enabled: false`, no TLS on HTTP or transport)\n- `audit-index` with 3 primary shards, 1 replica, and `require.tier: hot` shard allocation routing\n- `OnDelete` update strategy (manual pod-by-pod rollout required)\n- 512 MiB JVM heap, 5 Gi PVCs, 30s termination grace period\n- No snapshot repository configured\n- All ILM policies are built-in system policies; none applied to user indices\n\n**Key risks called out (Critical → Low):**\n1. Security completely disabled — unauthenticated plaintext HTTP access\n2. No snapshot/backup strategy — no restore path if upgrade fails\n3. All nodes master-eligible — sequential restarts are safe but have no buffer\n4. Heap undersized (40–62% used at idle), storage watermarks tight for 5 Gi PVCs\n5. `OnDelete` strategy requires strict manual coordination\n6. `cluster.initial_master_nodes` present (bootstrap-only setting, should be removed)\n\n**Plan includes:** pre-upgrade checklist, step-by-step rolling upgrade procedure, rollback plan, security enablement as a separate window, index settings impact assessment, and open questions for the SRE review."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":559,"cache_read_input_tokens":54284,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":559},"output_tokens":1,"servi